Method Detail

equivalence

public String equivalence(Namespace sourceNamespace,
                          String sourceValue,
                          Namespace targetNamespace)
                   throws EquivalencerException
Finds a parameter, equivalent to the sourceParameter, and found in the Namespace identified by targetNamespace.

Note: The first time any method in Equivalencer is called the equivalencing engine is instantiated, but only once. The equivalencing engine loads the BEL equivalence files associated with the framework and uses them do perform equivalencing.

Parameters:
sourceNamespace - Namespace, the namespace of the source parameter
sourceValue - String, the source parameter value
targetNamespace - Namespace, the namespace of the equivalent parameter to find
Returns:
the equivalent parameter found in targetNamespace, or null if no equivalent parameter is found in that namespace
Throws:
EquivalencerException - Thrown if an exception occurs finding the equivalent parameter

equivalence

public Map<Namespace,String> equivalence(Namespace sourceNamespace,
                                         String sourceValue)
                                  throws EquivalencerException
Finds all parameters equivalent to the sourceParameter.

Note: The first time any method in Equivalencer is called the equivalencing engine is instantiated, but only once. The equivalencing engine loads the BEL equivalence files associated with the framework and uses them do perform equivalencing.

Parameters:
sourceNamespace - Namespace, the namespace of the source parameter
sourceValue - String, the source parameter value
Returns:
the equivalent parameters or an empty map if no equivalent parameter is found
Throws:
EquivalencerException - Thrown if an exception occurs finding all equivalences

getUUID

public SkinnyUUID getUUID(Namespace namespace,
                          String value)
                   throws EquivalencerException
Obtain the equivalence UUID for the given namespace and value.

Parameters:
namespace - namespace, must not be null
value - value, must not be null
Returns:
UUID representing the value or null if the namespace/value combination has no equivalents. null is also returned if the namespace has no equivalences defined.
Throws:
EquivalencerException - Thrown if an exception occurs finding all equivalences
